], [[Colorado]]||A liberal radio show host who was murdered by a white nationalist group.<ref>{{cite news|last=Estes |first=Clarissa Pinkola |date=May 30, 2007 |url=http://themoderatevoice.com/religion/judaism/jews/13149/the-ironies-man-convicted-of-slaying-alan-berg-dies/ |title=The Ironies: White Supremacist Convicted of Slaying Alan Berg Dies |publisher=The Moderate Voice |access-date=December 6, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071215063142/http://themoderatevoice.com/religion/judaism/jews/13149/the-ironies-man-convicted-of-slaying-alan-berg-dies/ |archive-date=December 15, 2007 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|October 15, 1984}}||[[Henry Liu]] (a.k.a. Chiang Nan)||Freelancer and author||[[Daly City, California|Daly City]], California||A critic of the [[Kuomintang]] who was assassinated on the orders of the Kuomintang.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bishop|first=Katherine|title=California Jury Is Told Defendant Admitted Slaying Journalist |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1988/03/09/us/california-jury-is-told-defendant-admitted-slaying-journalist.html |newspaper=New York Times |date=March 9, 1988|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|August 9, 1987}}||[[Assassination of Vietnamese-American journalists in the United States|Tap Van Pham]] (a.k.a. Hoai Diep Tu)||''Mai''||[[Garden Grove, California|Garden Grove]], California||He was assassinated by arson while sleeping in his office by an anti-communist group that took responsibility.<ref name=ajr1993 /><ref name=propublica1 /><ref name=OCWeekly1 /><ref name=OCWeekly2 />\n|-\n|{{dts|November 22, 1989}}||[[Assassination of Vietnamese-American journalists in the United States|Nhan Trong Do]]||''Van Nghe Tien Phong''||[[Fairfax County, Virginia|Fairfax County]], Virginia||A layout designer who worked with Triet Le, he was the first employer of the Vietnamese-language magazine to be assassinated.<ref name=ajr1993 /><ref name=propublica1 /><ref name=OCWeekly1 /><ref name=OCWeekly2 /><ref name=nytimes-SEP1990 />\n|-\n|{{dts|September 22, 1990}}||[[Assassination of Vietnamese-American journalists in the United States|Triet Le]]||''Van Nghe Tien Phong''||[[Bailey's Crossroads, Virginia|Bailey's Crossroads]], Virginia||A columnist of controversial content for the same Vietnamese magazine that employed Nhan Trong Do. Assassinated.<ref name=ajr1993 /><ref name=propublica1 /><ref name=OCWeekly1>{{cite news|first=Nick |last=Schou |title=A History of Violence |url=http://www.ocweekly.com/2007-08-16/features/a-history-of-violence/ |newspaper=OC Weekly |date=August 16, 2007 |accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref><ref name=OCWeekly2>{{cite news|first=Nick |last=Schou |title=Red Scare in Little Saigon |url=http://www.ocweekly.com/2007-08-16/features/red-scare-in-little-saigon/2/ |newspaper=OC Weekly |date=August 16, 2007 |accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref><ref name=nytimes-SEP1990>{{cite news|first=B. Drummond|last=Ayres Jr |title=Slaying of Vietnamese Exiles in Washington Renews Refugee Fears |newspaper=New York Times | url=https://www.nytimes.com/1990/09/25/us/slaying-of-vietnamese-exiles-in-washington-renews-refugee-fears.html |date=September 25, 1990 |accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Political motives in two killings? |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=0CEuAAAAIBAJ&sjid=B_oDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4280,3223035&dq=triet+le&hl=en |newspaper=Spokane Chronicle |date=September 24, 1990 |accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|February 18, 1991}}||[[Assassinations of Little Haiti journalists|Jean-Claude Olivier]]||WLQY-AM (1320)||[[Little Haiti]], [[Miami]], [[Florida]]||A colleague of D'Or, he was known for his controversial commentary and was assassinated on his way to his car.<ref name=csmonitoronhaiti /><ref>{{cite news|agency=Associated Press |title=Controversial disc jockey shot to death |newspaper=The Victoria Advocate |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=DTxSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=njYNAAAAIBAJ&pg=7054,3568637&dq=jean+claude+olivier&hl=en|date=February 21, 1991 |accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|March 15, 1991}}||[[Fritz D'Or]]||[[WLQY|WLQY-AM (1320)]]||Little Haiti, Miami, Florida||A colleague of Olivier's at WLQY, he was assassinated as he left a club.<ref name=csmonitoronhaiti /><ref name=sunsentineldor>{{cite news|first=Monica |last=Rhor |title=Militant Haitian Activist Shot And Killed By Unidentified ManMilitant Haitian Activist Shot And Killed By Unidentified Man |url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1991-03-17/news/9101140028_1_haitian-american-haitian-refugee-center-unidentified-man-shot |publisher=Sun Sentinel |date=March 17, 1991 |accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|March 11, 1992}}||[[Manuel de Dios Unanue]]||''[[El Diario La Prensa]]''||[[Queens]], New York City, New York||Murdered by Colombian drug traffickers for writing about drug trade.<ref name=nydaily2002>{{cite news|first=Albor|last=Ruiz|title=Another Journalist Who Died In War |url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2002-03-07/local/18190709_1_dios-unanue-traffickers-cartel|newspaper=New York Daily News|date=March 7, 2002 |accessdate=September 23, 2012}}</ref><ref name=PeopleMagazine>{{cite magazine|last=Brock |first=Pope |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20112311,00.html |title=A Crusader Falls |magazine=People.com |date=March 30, 1992 |accessdate=November 2, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|October 24, 1993}}||[[Assassinations of Little Haiti journalists|Dona St. Plite]]||[[WQVN|WKAT]]||Little Haiti, Miami, Florida||St. Plite was attending a benefit for former colleague Fritz Dor when he was also assassinated for supporting [[Jean-Bertrand Aristide]].<ref name=csmonitoronhaiti>{{cite journal|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/1993/1027/27032.html |title=Haiti's Culture of Violence Extends to Miami / The Christian Science Monitor |journal=Christian Science Monitor |date=October 27, 1993 |accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref><ref name=sunsentinelstplite>{{cite web|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1993-10-26/news/9310260020_1_st-plite-haitian-commentator-s-death-president-jean-bertrand-aristide |title=Haitian Commentator's Death |publisher=Sun Sentinel |date=October 26, 1993 |accessdate=November 6, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|October 18, 2000}} ||[[James Edwin Richards]]||Citizen journalist, editor and publisher||[[Venice, Los Angeles]], California|| Richards was murdered at his Oakwood neighborhood home in the neighborhood where he had established himself as a citizen crime reporter.<ref name=abcnews>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/story?id=95310&page=1#.UFJybrJlRQQ |title=Was an LA Activist Shot for His Anti-Crime Efforts? \u2013 ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |accessdate=October 24, 2013|date=2006-01-07 }}</ref><ref name=death>{{cite news|first1=Gina |last1=Piccalo |first2=Kurt |last2=Streeter |title=Venice Anti-Gang Activist Killed in His Driveway |newspaper=LA Times |date=October 19, 2000 |accessdate=November 8, 2013 |url=https://articles.latimes.com/2000/oct/19/local/me-38801}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|September 11, 2001}}||[[Bill Biggart]]||Freelance photographer||[[Lower Manhattan]], New York City, New York||Killed while photographing the rescue effort outside the World Trade Center before the tower collapsed.<ref>{{cite news | first=Rome |last=Neal | title=Bill Biggart: Final Exposures | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2002/09/05/september11/main520940.shtml |publisher=CBS News |date=September 6, 2002  |accessdate=November 6, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|October 5, 2001}}||[[Robert Stevens (photo editor)|Robert Stevens]]||''[[Sun (supermarket tabloid)|Sun]]''||[[Boca Raton, Florida|Boca Raton]], Florida||Murdered as one of the media targets of the [[2001 anthrax attacks]] less than a month after 9/11.<ref>{{cite news|title=Chronology of 2001 anthrax events |url=http://www.sun-sentinel.com/news/local/palmbeach/sfl-1013anthraxchronology,0,4805314.story |publisher=sun-sentinel |date=December 24, 2012 |accessdate=December 26, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{dts|August 2, 