 in Annapolis Capital shooting as Jarrod Ramos, who had long-running feud with paper |last=Duncan |first=Ian |date=June 28, 2018 |work=Baltimore Sun |access-date=June 28, 2018 |last2=Bogel-Burroughs |first2=Nicholas |language=en-US}}</ref> Hiassen was an editor and columnist, Fischman was an editorial columnist, Winters was a features journalist. McNamara was a sports reporter for the ''Capital'' and the editor for the affiliated weekly ''Bowie Blade-News''. Also killed in the shooting was Rebecca Smith, a sales associate for Capital Gazette Communications.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Marbella |first1=Jean |title=Capital Gazette editor Rob Hiaasen identified as victim of shooting at newspaper |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/anne-arundel/bs-md-rob-hiaasen-20180628-story.html |website=baltimoresun.com |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Wenger |first1=Yvonne |title=Capital Gazette shooting victim Wendi Winters: A prolific writer who chronicled her community |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/anne-arundel/bs-md-wendi-winters-20180628-story.html |website=baltimoresun.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Cox |first1=Erin |title=Capital Gazette shooting victim Gerald Fischman: Clever and quirky voice of a community newspaper |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/anne-arundel/bs-md-gerald-fischman-20180628-story.html |website=baltimoresun.com |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=McDaniels |first1=Andrea K. |title=Capital Gazette shooting victim John McNamara: Sports reporting was his dream job |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/anne-arundel/bs-md-john-mcnamara-20180628-story.html |website=baltimoresun.com |accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Anderson |first1=Jessica |title=Capital Gazette shooting victim Rebecca Smith: Recent hire loved spending time with family |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/anne-arundel/bs-md-ar-rebecca-smith-20180628-story.html |website=baltimoresun.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Rob Hiaasen]]\n|-\n| [[John McNamara]]\n|-\n| Wendi Winters\n|}\n\n==Other journalists and media workers killed on 9/11==\nThe only professional, working journalist to die while covering the September 11 terrorist attacks on the [[World Trade Center (1973\u20132001)|World Trade Center]] in New York City was photojournalist [[Bill Biggart]], who was killed by falling debris as he was taking photographs.<ref name=irish>{{cite news|first=Conor |last=O'Clery |newspaper=The Irish Times |title=The parting shot |date=December 22, 2001 |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/weekend/2001/1222/01122200163.html}}</ref><ref name=Newsweek>{{cite magazine|first=Jerry |last=Adler |title=Shooting To the End |magazine=Newsweek |date=October 15, 2001 |accessdate=February 28, 2013 |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/newsweek/2001/10/14/shooting-to-the-end.html}}</ref> However, the [[International Federation of Journalists]], which also counts media workers, said that six other media workers and a journalist who were not working at the time died in the attacks. Among those media workers [[Bill Biggart#Context|listed]] as killed were six broadcast TV engineers, who worked inside a tower, and another professional photojournalist, who was a passenger on the first plane that was flown into the WTC.<ref name=CBS2001>{{cite news|title=100 Journalists Killed In 2001 |publisher=CBS News |date=February 11, 2009 |accessdate=March 1, 2011 |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/2100-202_162-321563.html}}</ref>\n\n* Rod Coppola, TV engineer for [[WNET|WNET-TV]], WTC (North Tower)<ref name=ifex2001>{{cite news |title=At Pakistan/Afghanistan Border; Journalist Among Dead and Media Workers Missing |publisher=IFEX.org |date=September 25, 2001 |url=http://www.ifex.org/2001/09/25/at_pakistan_afghanistan_border/ |access-date=March 6, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912072321/http://www.ifex.org/2001/09/25/at_pakistan_afghanistan_border/ |archive-date=September 12, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Donald DiFranco, TV engineer for [[WABC-TV]], WTC (North Tower)<ref name=ifex2001 /> \n* Steve Jacobson, TV engineer for [[WPIX|WPIX-TV]], WTC (North Tower)<ref name=ifex2001 /> \n* Bob Pattison, TV engineer for [[WCBS-TV]], WTC (North Tower)<ref name=CBS2001 /><ref name=ifex2001 />\n* Thomas Pecorelli, professional freelance photojournalist, American Airlines Flight 11 passenger<ref name=CBS2001 />\n* Isias Rivera, TV engineer for WCBS-TV, WTC (North Tower)<ref name=CBS2001 /><ref name=ifex2001 />\n* William Steckman, TV engineer for [[WNBC|WNBC-TV]], WTC (North Tower)<ref name=ifex2001 />\n\n== Gallery ==\n{{Commons category|Journalists killed in the United States}}\n{{Gallery\n| title = Journalists killed in the United States\n|File:Appletons' Lovejoy Elijah Parish.jpg|alt1=Elijah Parish Lovejoy (portrait)|<center>Elijah Parish Lovejoy</center>\n|File:James King of William, San Francisco editor.gif|alt2=James King of William (portrait)|<center>James King of William</center>\n|File:FrederickWadsworthLoring.jpg|alt3=Frederick Wadsworth Loring (portrait)|<center>Frederick Wadsworth Loring</center>\n|File:Markkellogg.jpg|alt4=Mark Kellogg (portrait)|<center>Mark Kellogg</center>\n|File:Charles de Young.jpg|alt5=Charles de Young (portrait)|<center>Charles de Young</center>\n|File:WCBrann.jpg|alt6=William Cowper Brann (portrait)|<center>William Cowper Brann</center>\n|File:Edward Ward Carmack.jpg|alt7=Edward Ward Carmack (portrait)|<center>Edward Ward Carmack</center>\n|File:Walter W Liggett.jpg|alt8=Walter W Liggett (portrait)|<center>Walter W Liggett</center>\n}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Censorship in the United States]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Journalists killed in the United States}}\n[[Category:Assassinated American journalists| ]]\n[[Category:Murder in the United States]]\n[[Category:Death in the United States-related lists|Journalists killed]]\n[[Category:Lists of journalists killed|United States]]\n[[Category:Lists of victims of crimes]]\n[[Category:United States crime-related lists]]\n[[Category:Censorship in the United States]]\n[[Category:Human rights in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toJohn McNamara(link changed toJohn McNamara, sportswriter) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_journalists_killed_in_the_United_States"}
{"title_page": "Peter J\u00f6rgensen", "text_new": "[[image:Joergensen Pedro.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Peter J\u00f6rgensen in Villarrica 1933, Photo by Poul (\"Pablo\") Schouboe]]\n\n'''Peter J\u00f6rgensen''' (\"Pedro Jorgensen\") (3 August 1870 in S\u00f8nderby, [[Assens Municipality|Funen]] &ndash; June 1937 in [[Villarrica, Paraguay]]) was a [[Danish people|Danish]] early 20th century [[entomology|entomologist]], active particularly in Argentina and Paraguay.\n\n== Life ==\nPeter J\u00f6rgensen was educated as a teacher of English and [[German language|German]] in [[Copenhagen]] 1889. In 1892 he contracted [[tuberculosis]] \u2014 a condition he suffered from throughout the remainder of his life. In 1906, he joined his friend [[Anders Christian Jensen-Haarup]] on a trip to the [[Mendoza Province]] in western [[Argentina]] in the hope that the arid [[Andes Mountains|Andean]] climate would be beneficial to his health. The two [[Natural history|naturalists]] made extensive [[insect]] collections, which were either sold (e.g. to the German entomologist [[Heinrich Friese]]<ref name=Friese1908>Friese 1908</ref>) to cover their travel expenses or were sent to specialists for identification. They also published short accounts (in [[Danish language|Danish]]) of their adventures in Argentina.\n\nJ\u00f6rgensen moved on to Paraguay, where he settled near Villarrica. He committed his life to a small farm and further entomological research. He also became a plant collector for several American museums. He was found murdered at his farm in June 1937.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* J\u00f8rgensen, P. (1906): Beitrag zur Biologie der Blattwespen (Chalastogastra). Zeitschrift f\u00fcr wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 2: 347-351.\n* J\u00f8rgensen, P. (1906): De danske Arter af Bladhvepsesl\u00e6gten Pontania Costa (Chalastogastra). - Entomologiske Meddelelser, 3: 113-126.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1909) Beobachtungen \u00fcber Blumenbesuch, Biologie, Verbreitung usw. Der Bienen von Mendoza. (Hym.). Teil I. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1909, Heft 1: 53-65. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1909_Beobachtungen_uber_Blumenbesuch.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1909) Beobachtungen \u00fcber Blumenbesuch, Biologie, Verbreitung usw. Der Bienen von Mendoza. (Hym.). Teil II. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1909, Heft 2: 211-227. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1909_Beobachtungen_uber_Blumenbesuch.pdf Full text]\n* Kieffer, J.J. & J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1910) Gallen und Gallentiere aus Argentinien. Zentralblatt f\u00fcr Bakteriologie und Parasitenkunde (Abt. 2), 27: 362-444. Here, a new species was described as ''Centrodiplosis falcigera'' Jorgensen & Kieffer, which Kieffer subsequently moved to a newly erected genus ''[[Jorgensenia]]'', named so in the honour of Peter J\u00f6rgensen.<ref>{{cite web |last=Yu |first=Dicky Sick Ki |url=http://www.taxapad.com/local.php?taxonidLC=87034031 |title=''Jorgensenia falcigera'' (Jorgensen & Kieffer 1910) |website=Home of Ichneumonoidea |publisher=Taxapad |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080032/http://www.taxapad.com/local.php?taxonidLC=87034031 |archive-date=March 4, 2016}}</ref>\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Los cris\u00eddidos y los Himen\u00f3pteros aculeatos de la Provincia de Mendoza. Anales del Museo Nacional de Buenos Aires, 22: 267-338. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1912_Los_crisididos_y_los_himenopteros.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Beitrag zur Biologie einiger s\u00fcdamerikanischer Bienen, Anhang. Beschreibung von Megalopta (Megaloptella) ipomoeae n. sp. Zeitschrift f\u00fcr wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 8: 268-272. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1912_Beitrag_zur_Biologie.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Revision der Apiden der Provinz Mendoza, Republica Argentina (Hym.). Zoologisches Jahrbuch, Abteilung f\u00fcr Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 32: 89-162. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1912_Revision_der_Apiden.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Berichtigungen und Erg\u00e4nzungen sur \"Revision der Apiden der Provinz Mendoza, Republica Argentina (Hym.)\". Zoologisches Jahrbuch, Abteilung f\u00fcr Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 33: 643-644.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1913): Los Tenthredinoidea (Hym.) de la Rep\u00fablica Argentina. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural, Buenos Aires, 24: 247-288 + 3 plates.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1916): Las mariposas Argentinas (Lepidoptera): familia Pieridae. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural, Buenos Aires, 28: 427-520.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1921): Sobre algunos nuevos enemigos de la yerba mat\u00e9, [[Ilex paraguariensis]]. Revista de la Sociedad Cient\u00edfica del Paraguay, Asunci\u00f3n, 2: 27-30.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1924): Sobre dos casos de hermafroditismo en las mariposas (Lepidoptera). Revista de la Sociedad Cient\u00edfica del Paraguay, Asunci\u00f3n, 1 (6): 89-90.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1924): Observaciones biol\u00f3gicas de Lepid\u00f3pteros sudamericanos. Revista de la Sociedad Cient\u00edfica del Paraguay, Asunci\u00f3n, 1 (6): 84-89.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1930): Los Castniidae de la Argentina y Paraguay. Revista de la Sociedad Entomol\u00f3gica Argentina, 3 (14): 175-180.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1932): Lepidopterologisches aus S\u00fcdamerika. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 46 (1): 37-66.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1934): Neue Schmetterlinge und Raupen aus S\u00fcdamerika. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 48: 60-78.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1935): Lepid\u00f3pteros nuevos o raros de la Argentina y del Paraguay. Anales del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia, Entomolog\u00eda, Buenos Aires, 38: 85-130 + 4 plates.\n\n== Legacy ==\nJ\u00f6rgensen's extensive collection activity in understudied regions and his meticulous descriptions of specimens resulted in numerous new species being described by himself and by specialists around the world, with whom he corresponded. [[Heinrich Friese]] described 143 new [[taxon|taxa]] of Argentine bees collected in part by J\u00f6rgensen and Jensen-Haarup.<ref name=Friese1908/> Also the British-American [[zoology|zoologist]] [[Theodore Dru Alison Cockerell]] received specimens from J\u00f6rgensen and erected new species based on them. Today, a small fraction of his collections are kept in the Zoological Museum of the [[University of Copenhagen]].\n\nThe monotypic [[ant lion]] genus ''[[Joergenia]]'' [[Peter Esben-Petersen|Esben-Petersen]] (1933) was named in his honour.<ref>The only species in the genus, ''Joergenia pulchra'' Esben-Petersen (1933), has been found in Paraguay only. It was considered to belong to the genus ''[[Eremoleon]]'' by Stange (1970, p. 20).</ref> Two [[gall midge]] genera are named for him: ''Jorgensenia'' Kieffer, 1913, and ''Jorgenseniella'' Maia, 2005 ([[Diptera]]: [[Cecidomyiidae]]).<ref>Gagn\u00e9, R.J. & M. Jaschhof (2014) A Catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World, 3rd edn. [https://www.ars.usda.gov/SP2UserFiles/Place/12454900/Gagne_2014_World_Cecidomyiidae_Catalog_3rd_Edition.pdf]</ref>\nA number of insect species have similarly been named for him, e.g. ''[[Pontania joergenseni]]'' Enslin 1916 ([[Tenthredinidae|Symphyta: Tenthredinidae]]), ''[[Tessella jorgenseni]]'' (Schaus, 1921) ([[Arctiidae|Lepidoptera: Arctiidae]]) and ''[[Eurota joergenseni]]'' Orfila, 1931 ([[Arctiidae|Lepidoptera: Arctiidae]]).\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n* Cockerell, T.D.A. (1909). A new bee of the genus ''Halictus'' from the Argentine. Flora og Fauna, 11: 9.\n* Friese, H. (1908) Die Apidae \"(Blumenwespen)\" von Argentina nach den Reisenergebnissen der Herren A. C. Jensen-Haarup und P. J\u00f6rgensen in den Jahren 1904-1907. Naturhistorisk Forening for Jylland, Silkeborg, 116 pp.\n* Esben-Petersen, P. (1933). New and little-known Neuroptera. Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening, 94: 109-123.\n* Lizer y Trelles, C. A. (1942). La coleccion Coccidologica de Pedro Jorgensen. Notas del Museo de la Plata 7: 69-80.\n* Rasmussen, Claus (2007) Anders Christian Jensen-Haarup & Peter J\u00f8rgensen.\n* Stange, L. A. (1970). Revision of the ant-lion tribe Brachynemurini of North America. Univ. California Publ. Ent. 55: 1-192.\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jorgensen, Peter}}\n[[Category:1870 births]]\n[[Category:1937 deaths]]\n[[Category:Danish entomologists]]\n[[Category:Hymenopterists]]\n[[Category:Danish lepidopterists]]\n[[Category:Danish people murdered abroad]]\n[[Category:People murdered in Paraguay]]\n[[Category:1937 murders in South America]]\n[[Category:1937 crimes in Paraguay]]\n[[Category:1930s murders in Paraguay]]\n", "text_old": "[[image:Joergensen Pedro.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Peter J\u00f6rgensen in Villarrica 1933, Photo by Poul (\"Pablo\") Schouboe]]\n\n'''Peter J\u00f6rgensen''' (\"Pedro Jorgensen\") (3 August 1870 in S\u00f8nderby, [[Assens Municipality|Funen]] &ndash; June 1937 in [[Villarrica, Paraguay]]) was a [[Danish people|Danish]] early 20th century [[entomology|entomologist]], active particularly in Argentina and Paraguay.\n\n== Life ==\nPeter J\u00f6rgensen was educated as a teacher of English and [[German language|German]] in [[Copenhagen]] 1889. In 1892 he acquired [[tuberculosis]] \u2014 a condition he suffered from throughout the remainder of his life. In 1906, he joined his friend [[Anders Christian Jensen-Haarup]] on a trip to the [[Mendoza Province]] in western [[Argentina]] in the hope that the arid [[Andes Mountains|Andean]] climate would be beneficial to his health. The two [[Natural history|naturalists]] made extensive [[insect]] collections, which were either sold (e.g. to the German entomologist [[Heinrich Friese]]<ref name=Friese1908>Friese 1908</ref>) to cover their travel expenses or were sent to specialists for identification. They also published short accounts (in [[Danish language|Danish]]) of their adventures in Argentina.\n\nJ\u00f6rgensen moved on to Paraguay, where he settled near Villarrica. He committed his life to a small farm and further entomological research. He also became a plant collector for several American museums. He was found murdered at his farm in June 1937.\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* J\u00f8rgensen, P. (1906): Beitrag zur Biologie der Blattwespen (Chalastogastra). Zeitschrift f\u00fcr wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 2: 347-351.\n* J\u00f8rgensen, P. (1906): De danske Arter af Bladhvepsesl\u00e6gten Pontania Costa (Chalastogastra). - Entomologiske Meddelelser, 3: 113-126.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1909) Beobachtungen \u00fcber Blumenbesuch, Biologie, Verbreitung usw. Der Bienen von Mendoza. (Hym.). Teil I. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1909, Heft 1: 53-65. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1909_Beobachtungen_uber_Blumenbesuch.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1909) Beobachtungen \u00fcber Blumenbesuch, Biologie, Verbreitung usw. Der Bienen von Mendoza. (Hym.). Teil II. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1909, Heft 2: 211-227. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1909_Beobachtungen_uber_Blumenbesuch.pdf Full text]\n* Kieffer, J.J. & J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1910) Gallen und Gallentiere aus Argentinien. Zentralblatt f\u00fcr Bakteriologie und Parasitenkunde (Abt. 2), 27: 362-444. Here, a new species was described as ''Centrodiplosis falcigera'' Jorgensen & Kieffer, which Kieffer subsequently moved to a newly erected genus ''[[Jorgensenia]]'', named so in the honour of Peter J\u00f6rgensen.<ref>{{cite web |last=Yu |first=Dicky Sick Ki |url=http://www.taxapad.com/local.php?taxonidLC=87034031 |title=''Jorgensenia falcigera'' (Jorgensen & Kieffer 1910) |website=Home of Ichneumonoidea |publisher=Taxapad |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080032/http://www.taxapad.com/local.php?taxonidLC=87034031 |archive-date=March 4, 2016}}</ref>\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Los cris\u00eddidos y los Himen\u00f3pteros aculeatos de la Provincia de Mendoza. Anales del Museo Nacional de Buenos Aires, 22: 267-338. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1912_Los_crisididos_y_los_himenopteros.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Beitrag zur Biologie einiger s\u00fcdamerikanischer Bienen, Anhang. Beschreibung von Megalopta (Megaloptella) ipomoeae n. sp. Zeitschrift f\u00fcr wissenschaftliche Insektenbiologie, 8: 268-272. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1912_Beitrag_zur_Biologie.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Revision der Apiden der Provinz Mendoza, Republica Argentina (Hym.). Zoologisches Jahrbuch, Abteilung f\u00fcr Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 32: 89-162. [http://biographies.melipona.org/Argentina/pdfs/PJ_1912_Revision_der_Apiden.pdf Full text]\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1912) Berichtigungen und Erg\u00e4nzungen sur \"Revision der Apiden der Provinz Mendoza, Republica Argentina (Hym.)\". Zoologisches Jahrbuch, Abteilung f\u00fcr Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 33: 643-644.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1913): Los Tenthredinoidea (Hym.) de la Rep\u00fablica Argentina. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural, Buenos Aires, 24: 247-288 + 3 plates.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1916): Las mariposas Argentinas (Lepidoptera): familia Pieridae. Anales del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural, Buenos Aires, 28: 427-520.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1921): Sobre algunos nuevos enemigos de la yerba mat\u00e9, [[Ilex paraguariensis]]. Revista de la Sociedad Cient\u00edfica del Paraguay, Asunci\u00f3n, 2: 27-30.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1924): Sobre dos casos de hermafroditismo en las mariposas (Lepidoptera). Revista de la Sociedad Cient\u00edfica del Paraguay, Asunci\u00f3n, 1 (6): 89-90.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1924): Observaciones biol\u00f3gicas de Lepid\u00f3pteros sudamericanos. Revista de la Sociedad Cient\u00edfica del Paraguay, Asunci\u00f3n, 1 (6): 84-89.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1930): Los Castniidae de la Argentina y Paraguay. Revista de la Sociedad Entomol\u00f3gica Argentina, 3 (14): 175-180.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1932): Lepidopterologisches aus S\u00fcdamerika. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 46 (1): 37-66.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1934): Neue Schmetterlinge und Raupen aus S\u00fcdamerika. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 48: 60-78.\n* J\u00f6rgensen, P. (1935): Lepid\u00f3pteros nuevos o raros de la Argentina y del Paraguay. Anales del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia, Entomolog\u00eda, Buenos Aires, 38: 85-130 + 4 plates.\n\n== Legacy ==\nJ\u00f6rgensen's extensive collection activity in understudied regions and his meticulous descriptions of specimens resulted in numerous new species being described by himself and by specialists around the world, with whom he corresponded. [[Heinrich Friese]] described 143 new [[taxon|taxa]] of Argentine bees collected in part by J\u00f6rgensen and Jensen-Haarup.<ref name=Friese1908/> Also the British-American [[zoology|zoologist]] [[Theodore Dru Alison Cockerell]] received specimens from J\u00f6rgensen and erected new species based on them. Today, a small fraction of his collections are kept in the Zoological Museum of the [[University of Copenhagen]].\n\nThe monotypic [[ant lion]] genus ''[[Joergenia]]'' [[Peter Esben-Petersen|Esben-Petersen]] (1933) was named in his honour.<ref>The only species in the genus, ''Joergenia pulchra'' Esben-Petersen (1933), has been found in Paraguay only. It was considered to belong to the genus ''[[Eremoleon]]'' by Stange (1970, p. 20).</ref> Two [[gall midge]] genera are named for him: ''Jorgensenia'' Kieffer, 1913, and ''Jorgenseniella'' Maia, 2005 ([[Diptera]]: [[Cecidomyiidae]]).<ref>Gagn\u00e9, R.J. & M. Jaschhof (2014) A Catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World, 3rd edn. [https://www.ars.usda.gov/SP2UserFiles/Place/12454900/Gagne_2014_World_Cecidomyiidae_Catalog_3rd_Edition.pdf]</ref>\nA number of insect species have similarly been named for him, e.g. ''[[Pontania joergenseni]]'' Enslin 1916 ([[Tenthredinidae|Symphyta: Tenthredinidae]]), ''[[Tessella jorgenseni]]'' (Schaus, 1921) ([[Arctiidae|Lepidoptera: Arctiidae]]) and ''[[Eurota joergenseni]]'' Orfila, 1931 ([[Arctiidae|Lepidoptera: Arctiidae]]).\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n* Cockerell, T.D.A. (1909). A new bee of the genus ''Halictus'' from the Argentine. Flora og Fauna, 11: 9.\n* Friese, H. (1908) Die Apidae \"(Blumenwespen)\" von Argentina nach den Reisenergebnissen der Herren A. C. Jensen-Haarup und P. J\u00f6rgensen in den Jahren 1904-1907. Naturhistorisk Forening for Jylland, Silkeborg, 116 pp.\n* Esben-Petersen, P. (1933). New and little-known Neuroptera. Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening, 94: 109-123.\n* Lizer y Trelles, C. A. (1942). La coleccion Coccidologica de Pedro Jorgensen. Notas del Museo de la Plata 7: 69-80.\n* Rasmussen, Claus (2007) Anders Christian Jensen-Haarup & Peter J\u00f8rgensen.\n* Stange, L. A. (1970). Revision of the ant-lion tribe Brachynemurini of North America. Univ. California Publ. Ent. 55: 1-192.\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jorgensen, Peter}}\n[[Category:1870 births]]\n[[Category:1937 deaths]]\n[[Category:Danish entomologists]]\n[[Category:Hymenopterists]]\n[[Category:Danish lepidopterists]]\n[[Category:Danish people murdered abroad]]\n[[Category:People murdered in Paraguay]]\n[[Category:1937 murders in South America]]\n[[Category:1937 crimes in Paraguay]]\n[[Category:1930s murders in Paraguay]]\n", "name_user": "Daddyman1962", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLife", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_J%C3%B6rgensen"}
{"title_page": "Olli Malmivaara", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| image = Malmivaara Olli Blues 2013 1.jpg\n| caption =\n| image_size = 225px\n| team = [[Espoo Blues]]\n| league = [[Liiga]] \n| former_teams = [[Jokerit]]<br>[[SaiPa]]<br>[[New Jersey Devils]]<br>[[JYP Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4]]\n| position = [[Defenceman]]\n| shoots = Left\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 7\n| weight_lb = 230\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|3|13}}\n| birth_place = [[Kajaani]], [[Finland]]\n| draft = 117th overall\n| draft_year = 2000\n| draft_team = [[Chicago Blackhawks]]\n| career_start = 2007\n}}\n'''Olli Malmivaara''' (born March 13, 1982) is a [[Finnish people|Finnish]] retired professional [[ice hockey]] [[defenceman]]. He played in the [[National Hockey League]] for the [[New Jersey Devils]].\n\n==Biography==\nAs a youth, Malmivaara played in the 1995 [[Quebec International Pee-Wee Hockey Tournament]] with a team from [[J\u00e4rvenp\u00e4\u00e4]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publicationsports.com/ressources/files/439/Joueurs_Pro.pdf|title=Pee-Wee players who have reached NHL or WHA|year=2018|website=Quebec International Pee-Wee Hockey Tournament|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref>\n\nHe later played in [[Jokerit]] where he made his [[SM-liiga]] debut; in 2003 he signed with [[SaiPa]] and spent two years with that team.{{citation needed|date=February 2019}} Malmivaara was drafted by the [[Chicago Blackhawks]] as their fourth-round pick, #117 overall, in the [[2000 NHL Entry Draft]].{{citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nIn 2006, he signed with the [[New Jersey Devils]] of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL). Malmivaara was a physical defenceman in the Finnish league, where he racked up an average of over 100 penalty minutes a season. The Devils signed him looking for defensive depth in Lowell. He played his first NHL game on October 31, 2007 against the [[Tampa Bay Lightning]] in a 6\u20131 win where he played just over 10 minutes. He would only play one other game in the [[2007\u201308 NHL season]], dressing for seven and a half minutes against the [[Toronto Maple Leafs]] in a 3\u20132 win.{{citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nAs of 2013, he is playing with the [[Espoo Blues]] in the Finnish [[Liiga]].<ref>{{citeweb| url = https://twitter.com/Espoo_Blues/status/328785024121982976 | title = Blues announce Malmivaara acquisition | publisher = [[Twitter]] | author = [[Espoo Blues]] | date = 2013-04-29 | accessdate = 2013-04-29}}</ref>\n\nMalmivaara's sister [[Laura Malmivaara|Laura]] is an actress.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hs.fi/kuukausiliite/art-2000002678490.html |title=N\u00e4yttelij\u00e4 Laura Malmivaara pelk\u00e4\u00e4 j\u00e4\u00e4kiekkoilijaveljens\u00e4 puolesta |last1=Kaartamo |first1=Outi |date=October 5, 2013 |website=[[Helsingin Sanomat]] |publisher=[[Sanoma]] Media Finland |language=Finnish |access-date=March 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Regular season]] \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Playoffs]] \n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! [[Season (sports)|Season]] \n! Team \n! League \n! GP \n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]] \n! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]] \n! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]] \n! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]] \n! GP\n! G \n! A \n! Pts \n! PIM \n|- \n| 1997\u201398\n| KJT U16\n| Jr. C SM-sarja\n| 22 || 3 || 7 || 10 || 6\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-  bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1998\u201399\n| Jokerit U18\n| Jr. B SM-sarja\n| 35 || 1 || 8 || 9 || 10\n| 7 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 2\n|-\n| 1999\u201300\n| Jokerit U18\n| Jr. B SM-sarja\n| 14 || 6 || 6 || 12 || 14\n| 1 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 2\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\"\n| 1999\u201300\n| Jokerit U20\n| Jr. A SM-liiga\n| 27 || 3 || 3 || 6 || 12\n| 12 || 0 || 2 || 2 || 2