enter\" | 680\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 38\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 47\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 85\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 766\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 91\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 5\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 4\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 9\n! ALIGN=\"center\" | 84\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Eliteprospects}}\n*{{hockeydb|51197}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Malmivaara, Olli}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chicago Blackhawks draft picks]]\n[[Category:Espoo Blues players]]\n[[Category:Finnish ice hockey defencemen]]\n[[Category:Jokerit players]]\n[[Category:JYP Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4 players]]\n[[Category:Lowell Devils players]]\n[[Category:New Jersey Devils players]]\n[[Category:People from Kajaani]]\n[[Category:SaiPa players]]\n\n\n{{Finland-icehockey-defenceman-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| image = Malmivaara Olli Blues 2013 1.jpg\n| caption =\n| image_size = 225px\n| team = [[Espoo Blues]]\n| league = [[Liiga]] \n| former_teams = [[Jokerit]]<br>[[SaiPa]]<br>[[New Jersey Devils]]<br>[[JYP Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4]]\n| position = [[Defenceman]]\n| shoots = Left\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 7\n| weight_lb = 230\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|3|13}}\n| birth_place = [[Kajaani]], [[Finland]]\n| draft = 117th overall\n| draft_year = 2000\n| draft_team = [[Chicago Blackhawks]]\n| career_start = 2007\n}}\n'''Olli Malmivaara''' (born March 13, 1982) is a [[Finnish people|Finnish]] retired professional [[ice hockey]] [[defenceman]]. He played in the [[National Hockey League]] for the [[New Jersey Devils]].\n\n==Biography==\nAs a youth, Malmivaara played in the 1995 [[Quebec International Pee-Wee Hockey Tournament]] with a team from [[J\u00e4rvenp\u00e4\u00e4]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publicationsports.com/ressources/files/439/Joueurs_Pro.pdf|title=Pee-Wee players who have reached NHL or WHA|year=2018|website=Quebec International Pee-Wee Hockey Tournament|access-date=2019-02-10}}</ref>\n\nHe later played in [[Jokerit]] where he made his [[SM-liiga]] debut; in 2003 he signed with [[SaiPa]] and spent two years with that team.{{citation needed|date=February 2019}} Malmivaara was drafted by the [[Chicago Blackhawks]] as their fourth-round pick, #117 overall, in the [[2000 NHL Entry Draft]].{{citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nIn 2006, he signed with the [[New Jersey Devils]] of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL). Malmivaara was a physical defenceman in the Finnish league, where he racked up an average of over 100 penalty minutes a season. The Devils signed him looking for defensive depth in Lowell. He played his first NHL game on October 31, 2007 against the [[Tampa Bay Lightning]] in a 6\u20131 win where he played just over 10 minutes. He would only play one other game in the [[2007\u201308 NHL season]], dressing for seven and a half minutes against the [[Toronto Maple Leafs]] in a 3-2 win.{{citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nAs of 2013, he is playing with the [[Espoo Blues]] in the Finnish [[Liiga]].<ref>{{citeweb| url = https://twitter.com/Espoo_Blues/status/328785024121982976 | title = Blues announce Malmivaara acquisition | publisher = [[Twitter]] | author = [[Espoo Blues]] | date = 2013-04-29 | accessdate = 2013-04-29}}</ref>\n\nMalmivaara's sister [[Laura Malmivaara|Laura]] is an actress.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hs.fi/kuukausiliite/art-2000002678490.html |title=N\u00e4yttelij\u00e4 Laura Malmivaara pelk\u00e4\u00e4 j\u00e4\u00e4kiekkoilijaveljens\u00e4 puolesta |last1=Kaartamo |first1=Outi |date=October 5, 2013 |website=[[Helsingin Sanomat]] |publisher=[[Sanoma]] Media Finland |language=Finnish |access-date=March 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Regular season]] \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=